snippet.title: T-Mobile Concord
snippet.description: The T-Mobile Concord's midrange specs won't turn any heads, but it's a reliable, stylish, and inexpensive handset that doesn't require a contract.

snippet.title: Samsung Flight
snippet.description: The Samsung Flight offers a unique, likable design and a fair number of features, but some performance gaps keep it from playing in the big leagues.

snippet.title: Wallops Flight Facility, NASA's hidden launch shop
snippet.description: Road Trip 2010: On the Atlantic coast of Virginia, the space agency uses a 6,000-acre facility to build and launch rockets and design high-altitude scientific balloons big enough to hold a sports stadium.

snippet.title: Solar Impulse 2 aims for round-the-world flight
snippet.description: The aircraft's lengthy wings are outfitted with 17,000 solar cells that will power it during a trip around the world next year.

snippet.title: Samsung Flight II SGH-A927 (AT&T)
snippet.description: The Samsung Flight II may have decent multimedia features, but its overall sluggishness keeps us from recommending it.

snippet.title: Lufthansa plans to beam in-flight movies to your devices
snippet.description: The airline's BoardConnect entertainment system can stream in-flight movies directly to Android, iOS, or Windows Phone devices.

snippet.title: Are in-flight phone calls in our future?
snippet.description: The FCC considers lifting the ban on cell phone use on airplanes, Walmart prepares for a Black Friday battle against Amazon, and some early Xbox One owners have defective systems.

snippet.title: Shovels sharpened for Google's flight terminal
snippet.description: Anchored by Google's own air force, the biggest new terminal for private jets to be built in 30 years will begin construction at San Jose International in January.
